<!-- DEV-note: Each section contains a single background container.
 It controls background colors, the containers width (and therefore the max width of inner containers) and special margin settings.
 Later on this container will control background images and background videos.

 By default this container is transparent and uses full width.
 Possible style classes are:

 - "section--reducedWidth" => Sets the outer width of the container to the sites max-width (currently 1440px)
 - "section--colorTheme[theme number 1-12]" => Sets the background color of the container
 - "section--removeSidePaddings" => Removes the left and right paddings of COLORED background container to achieve real full viewport views (e.g. for full width stages)
-->
<div class="section">

	<!-- DEV-note: The section might control visual and functional effects for the whole section.
	 This might be an inPage navigation or parallax effects. All effects must be controlled by data attributes.
	 The section itself shouldn't have any style classes!

	 Possible attributes are:

	 - "data-navlabel" => "String": Sets the name for the automatically generated in-page navigation. Also works as the anchor for that navigation. Default: none
	 - "data-parallax" => "true|false": Enables the parallax effect for this section. Default: false
	 - "data-parallax-offset" => "100": Sets how far bottom of a section should be above the bottom [in px] of viewport before parallax effect kicks in for that section. Default: 100
	 -->
	<section>
		<!-- DEV-note: The grid row defines the content width. But it is always limited by its surrounding background container.
		 It is possible to stack an unlimeted number of rows below each other.

		 By default each row uses full width and has no paddings/margins activated.
		 Possible style classes are:

		 - "row--reducedWidth" => Sets the outer width of the container to the sites max-width (currently 1440px)
		-->
		<div class="row row--reducedWidth">

			<!-- DEV-note: Each grid "row" has at least a column class "col". This is the default 100% full width container.
			 All grid columns collapse to 100% width either at 768px (medium) or 1024px (large).

			 !!! columns and offsets must have the same collapsing definition, both medium or both large !!!

			 Following grid columns are available:

			 - "col" => Adds a 12 "grid-columns" wide column - 100% width - 1 per row
			 - "col--[medium|large]-8" => Adds a 6 "grid-columns" wide column - 66.7% width - 1 per row
			 - "col--[medium|large]-6" => Adds a 6 "grid-columns" wide column - 50% width - 2 per row
			 - "col--[medium|large]-4" => Adds a 4 "grid-columns" wide column - 33.3% width - 3 per row
			 - "col--[medium|large]-3" => Adds a 3 "grid-columns" wide column - 25% width - 4 per row
			 - "col--[medium|large]-2" => Adds a 2 "grid-columns" wide column - 16.7% width - 6 per row
			 - "col--[medium|large]-offset-[1-10]" => Moves the column to the right by given count of columns
			-->
			{{bioInclude 'components/framework/grid/includes/demo.grid.1col' }}

		</div>
	</section>
</div>


